Package ohos.event.commonevent

Class CommonEventPublishInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.event.commonevent.CommonEventPublishInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sequenceable

    public final class CommonEventPublishInfo
extends Object
implements Sequenceable
    Provides information for publishing common events, including setting subscriber filter criteria, common event type and mode.

    If you call the CommonEventManager#publishCommonEvent(CommonEventData, CommonEventPublishInfo) or CommonEventManager#publishCommonEvent(CommonEventData, CommonEventPublishInfo, CommonEventSubscriber) method to publish a common event, you can publish the common event only to related subscribers by setting the filter criteria, including the user ID and permissions.

    If you call the setOrdered(boolean) method with a value of true, an ordered common event will be published. If you call the setSticky(boolean) method with a value of true, a sticky common event will be published. If you call either of the two methods with a value of false, a standard common event will be published by default. You can allow only specified subscribers to receive a common event by calling the setSubscriberPermissions(java.lang.String[]) method.

    Since:
    1
    See Also:
    CommonEventManager.publishCommonEvent(CommonEventData, CommonEventPublishInfo), CommonEventManager.publishCommonEvent(CommonEventData, CommonEventPublishInfo, CommonEventSubscriber)

        Sets whether the type of a common event is sticky or not.

        A sticky common event can be received by subscribers immediately after subscription. You are advised not to set a common event to be sticky.

        Parameters:
        sticky - Specifies whether the common event is sticky. The value true indicates sticky and the value false indicates standard.

      • setOrdered

        public void setOrdered​(boolean ordered)
        Sets whether the type of a common event is ordered or not.

        An ordered common event is received by subscribers in descending priority. Specifically, a highest-priority subscriber receives the event, then high-priority subscribers, and finally low-priority subscribers. priority limit -1000~1000 and the highest priority is 1000.

        Parameters:
        ordered - Specifies whether the common event is ordered. The value true indicates ordered and the value false indicates standard.
        Since:
        1

      • setSubscriberPermissions

        public void setSubscriberPermissions​(String[] subscriberPermissions)
        Sets permissions for subscribers. Only subscribers with required permissions can receive published common events.

        Currently, only one permission can be set for subscribers. If multiple permissions are specified in subscriberPermissions, only the first one takes effect.

        Parameters:
        subscriberPermissions - Indicates the permissions to be set. This parameter is optional. If it is specified, the value must be permissions that have been defined in the system.
        Since:
        1
